results.name: Number of Dyck paths of semilength n having exactly three (possibly overlapping) occurrences of the consecutive step pattern given by the binary expansion of n, where 1=U=(1,1) and 0=D=(1,-1).
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 5..200
example: a(6) = 5: UUDDUUDDUUDD, UUDDUUDUUDDD, UUDUUDDDUUDD, UUDUUDDUUDDD, UUDUUDUUDDDD.
results.author: _Alois P. Heinz_, Jun 10 2014
